    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Python Silence Traceback on Ctrl+c]]></title>
    <link href="http://saketkc.github.io/blog/2014/11/19/python-silence-traceback-on-ctrl-plus-c/"/>
    <updated>2014-11-19T00:44:50-08:00</updated>
    <id>http://saketkc.github.io/blog/2014/11/19/python-silence-traceback-on-ctrl-plus-c</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>I came across this small little hack while 
writing my downloader for NCBI-SRA datasets(Should be on PyPI soon!)</p>

<p><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='python'><span class='line'><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">signal</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="n">signal</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">signal</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">signal</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">SIGINT</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">y</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">sys</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">exit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">))</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<h3 id="what-did-we-just-do">What did we just do?</h3>
<p>using <code>signal.signal()</code> I set the <code>handler</code> to <code>sys.exit(0)</code> for <code>signal.SIGINT</code>
which is translated to a <code>KeyBoardInterrupt</code> exception(invoked on a <code>Ctrl+C</code> press)</p>

<p>Read more about the <code>signal</code> module <a href="https://docs.python.org/2/library/signal.html">here</a>.</p>
